{
  "name": "Fear",
  "_id": "matSplFear000000",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Each creature in a 30-foot Cone must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or drop whatever it is holding and have the &amp;Reference[frightened apply=false] condition for the duration.</p><p>A Frightened creature takes the &amp;Reference[dash] action and moves away from you by the safest route on each of its turns unless there is nowhere to move. If the creature ends its turn in a space where it doesn't have line of sight to you, the creature makes a Wisdom saving throw. On a successful save, the spell ends on that creature.</p><p><strong>Using a Higher-Level Spell Slot.</strong> If you cast this spell using a level 6+ spell slot, the spell is a 30-foot radius rather than cone and you choose each creature that spell targets.</p>",
